   School description front en

A word from the Director Alexandre Joux

   EJCAM, the School of Journalism and Communication of Aix-Marseille
   University is renowned for its training in journalism, in communication
   and media studies. EJCAM proposes high quality degree tailored to
   market needs and the workplace. It ensures that each of its master’s
   degree is a gateway into the professional world. The school is proud of
   its record of work placement: about eighty-five percent of its students
   are offered employment upon completing their degrees. Seventy-nine
   percent of those secure long-term employment contracts (CDI). The
   average waiting period before first work placement is only 4 months.

   Located in the beautiful mediterranean region south of France, the
   School of Journalism and Communication (EJCAM) is one of the many
   components of Aix-Marseille University. The school was founded in 1982
   and has been offering first-class training in media and communication
   studies. Equipped with modern state-of-the-art video, audio production
   and editing facilities (radio and TV production studios, multimedia and
   computer rooms), the school enrolls more than 500 students each year in
   its graduate and master’s degree programs.
   > learn more

